{"id":"R-3-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"Directly connecting the output of a register to the clock pins of other registers is prohibited. Note: If such a scenario occurs, measures such as clock network driving can be adopted.","Violation Examples":["module test (clk_40m, in1, in2, out1 );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\noutput reg out1;\n\nreg tmp1;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m)\ntmp1 <= in1;\n\nalways @ ( posedge tmp1 )//Violation1\nout1 <= in2;\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module test (clk_40m, in1, in2, out1 );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\noutput reg out1;\n\nreg tmp1;\nwire clk_tmp;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m)\ntmp1 <= in1;\n\nBUFG inclk_inst (.I(tmp1), .O(clk_tmp));\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_tmp )//Compliance 1\nout1 <= in2;\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-3-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"Connecting clock signals to signal pins other than the clock pins of registers is prohibited. Note: For example, connecting to data ports or reset ports is not allowed.","Violation Examples":["module test (clk_30m, clk_40m, rst_n, in1, out1, out2 );\ninput clk_30m;\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in1;\noutput reg out1;\noutputreg out2;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_30m)\nif ( !rst )\nout1 <=0;\nelse\nout1 <= in1;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m)\nif ( !rst )\nout2 <=0;\nelse\nout2 <= clk_30m;//Violation1\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-3-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"Using the output of combinational logic as a clock signal is prohibited. Assigning constants to clock signals is also prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top (clk_40m, ctrl, d1, d2, out1, out2 );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput ctrl;\ninput d1;\ninput d2;\noutput out1;\noutput out2;\n\nwire and_clk_40m;\n\nassign and_clk_40m = ctrl & d1;\nalways @ ( posedge and_clk_40m )//Violation1\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top( clk_40m, ctrl, d1, d2, out1, out2 );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput ctrl;\ninput d1;\ninput d2;\noutput out1;\noutput out2;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m )//Compliance 1\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"A-3-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"Simultaneous use of the rising edge and falling edge of a clock is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["module test (clk_40m, rst_n, in, out);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in;\noutput reg out;\n\nregtemp;\n\nalways @ (posedge clk_40m)//Violation1\nif (!rst_n)\ntemp <= 1'b0;\nelse\ntemp <= in;\n\nalways @ (negedge clk_40m)//Violation2\nif (!rst_n)\nout <= 1'b0;\nelse\nout <= temp;\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-3-2","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"It is recommended to create an independent module for the clock generation circuit.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-3-3","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"Using gated clocks is discouraged. Note: If gated clocks must be used, measures such as creating an independent gated clock generation circuit at the top level can be adopted.","Violation Examples":["module buffer (clk_40m, en, din, dout);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput en;\ninput din;\noutput reg dout;\n\nwire ce;\n\nassign ce = clk_40m & en;\n\nalways @(posedge ce)//Violation1\ndout <= din;\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-3-4","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Clock","category_key":"clock","description":"It is recommended to use only one clock domain.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-4-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"Connecting asynchronous set/reset signals to non-set/reset pins is prohibited.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-4-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"Using both asynchronous reset and synchronous reset in the same reset line is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module test (clk_40m, rst_n, in1, in2, out1, out2);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\noutput reg out1;\noutput reg out2;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n)\nbegin\nif ( !rst_n )\nout1 <= 1'b0;\nelse\nout1 <= in1;\nend\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m)//Violation1\nif ( !rst_n )\nout2 <= 1'b0;\nelse\nout2 <= in2;\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module test (clk_40m, rst_n, in1, in2, out1, out2);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\noutput reg out1;\noutput reg out2;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n)\nbegin\nif ( !rst_n )\nout1 <= 1'b0;\nelse\nout1 <= in1;\nend\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n)//Compliance 1\nif ( !rst_n )\nout2 <= 1'b0;\nelse\nout2 <= in2;\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-4-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"Using the output of combinational logic with race hazards as a reset signal is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top ( clk_40m, rsta_n, rstb_n, data, qout );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rsta_n;\ninput rstb_n;\ninput data;\noutput reg qout;\n\nwire rst_n;\n\nassign rst_n = rsta_n | rstb_n;//Violation1\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )\nbegin\nif ( !rst_n )\nqout <= 1'b0;\nelse\nqout <= data;\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-4-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"It is recommended to create an independent module for the reset generation circuit.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-4-2","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"Inserting logical operations into asynchronous reset lines is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["module top ( clk_40m, rst_n , data, sel, qout );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput data;\ninput sel;\noutput reg qout;\n\nwire rst_n_in;\n\nassign rst_n_in = rst_n & sel;//Violation1\ndff1 u1( . clk_40m (clk_40m), .rst_n(rst_n_in), .d(data), .q(qout) );\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-4-3","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"Using internally generated signals as asynchronous reset signals for registers is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["module top ( clk_40m, rst_n, in1, data, qout );\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in1;\ninput data;\noutput reg qout;\n\nreg rega;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )\nif ( !rst_n )\nrega <= 1'b0;\nelse\nrega <= in1;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rega )//Violation1\nif ( ! rega )\nqout <= 1'b0;\nelse\nqout <= data;\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-4-4","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"Simultaneous use of asynchronous set and asynchronous reset signals is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["module top(clk_40m, rst_n, set, data, qout);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput set;\ninput data;\noutput reg qout;\n…\nalways @( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n or posedge set )//Violation1\nbegin\nif ( ! rst_n )\nqout <= 1'b0;\nelse if ( set )\nqout <= 1'b1;\nelse\nqout <= data;\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top(clk_40m, rst_n, set, data, qout);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput set;\ninput data;\noutput reg qout;\n…\nalways @( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )//Compliance 1\nbegin\nif ( ! rst_n )\nqout <= 1'b0;\nelse if ( set )\nqout <= 1'b1;\nelse\nqout <= data;\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"A-4-5","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Reset","category_key":"reset","description":"It is recommended to use only one reset signal in the same always statement.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-5-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Flip-Flop","category_key":"ff","description":"Mixing flip-flops with reset and flip-flops without reset in the same always statement is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top ( clk_40m,rst_n,data_a,data_b,qout1,qout2);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput data_a;\ninput data_b;\noutput reg qout1;\noutput regqout2;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )\nbegin\nif ( ! rst_n )\nqout1 <= 1'b0;\nelse begin\nqout1 <= data_a;\nqout2 <= data_b;//Violation1\nend\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top(clk_40m, rst_n,data_a,data_b, qout1,qout2);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput data_a;\ninput data_b;\noutput reg qout1;\noutput regqout2;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )\nbegin\nif ( ! rst_n )\nbegin//Compliance 1\nqout1 <= 1'b0;\nqout2 <= 1'b0;\nend\nelse\nbegin\nqout1 <= data_a;\nqout2 <= data_b;\nend\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-5-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Flip-Flop","category_key":"ff","description":"Flip-flops must be initialized with an initial value during reset or initialization.","Violation Examples":["module top( clk_40m, qout);\ninput clk_40m;\noutput [3:0] qout;\n\nreg [3:0]counter;\n\nalways @( posedge clk_40m)\nbegin\ncounter <= counter + 1'b1;//Violation1\nend\n\nassign qout = counter;\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top( clk_40m, rst_n,qout);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\noutput [3:0]qout;\n\nreg [3:0]counter;\n\nalways @( posedge clk_40m)\nbegin\nif ( !rst_n )//Compliance 1\ncounter <= 4'b0;\nelse\ncounter <= counter + 1'b1;\nend\n\nassign qout = counter;\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-5-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Flip-Flop","category_key":"ff","description":"The trigger condition and entry condition of the reset signal must be consistent.","Violation Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n)\nbegin\nif ( rst_n )//Violation1\nqout<= 1'b0;\nelse\nqout <= data;\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n)\nbegin\nif(!rst_n )//Compliance 1\nqout <= 1'b0;\nelse\nqout <= data;\nend"]}
{"id":"R-6-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Latch","category_key":"latch","description":"Combinational logic loops containing latches are prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top( in1, in2, en, out1 );\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\ninput en;\noutput reg out1;\n\nwire temp;\n\nassign temp = ! (in1 & in2 & out1);//Violation1\n\nalways @( en or temp )\nbegin\nif ( en)\nout1 = temp;//Violation2\nelse\nout1 = out1;\nend\n\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-6-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Latch","category_key":"latch","description":"Describing latches using basic logic gates is prohibited. Note: Basic logic gates include AND gates, NOT gates, OR gates, etc.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-6-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Latch","category_key":"latch","description":"It is recommended to describe latches separately from other combinational logic circuits.","Violation Examples":["module top( data, start, en, dout1, dout2 );\ninput data;\ninput start;\ninput en;\noutput reg dout1;\noutput reg dout2;\n\nalways @( data, start, en )\nbegin\nif ( en )\ndout1 = data;\nelse\ndout1 = dout1;\n\ndout2 = data | start;//Violation1\nend\n\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top( data, start, en, dout1, dout2 );\ninput data;\ninput start;\ninput en;\noutput reg dout1;\noutput reg dout2;\n\nalways @( data, en )\nbegin\nif ( en )\ndout1 = data;\nelse\ndout1 = dout1;\nend\n\nalways @( data, start )//Compliance 1\nbegin\ndout2 = data | start;\nend\n\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-8-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"The data bit widths of the left and right operands of a relational operator must be consistent.","Violation Examples":["wire [7:0] w_slot_a;\nwire [5:0] w_slot_b;\nwire [7:0] w_slot_c;\nwire [7:0] w_or;\n\nassign w_or = (w_slot_a<= w_slot_b) ? w_slot_a : w_slot_c; //Violation1"],"Compliance Examples":["wire [7:0] w_slot_a;\nwire [7:0] w_slot_b;\nwire [7:0] w_slot_c;\nwire [7:0] w_or;\n\nassign w_or = (w_slot_a<= w_slot_b) ? w_slot_a : w _slot_c;//Compliance 1"]}
{"id":"R-8-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"The data bit widths of the left and right operands of a bitwise operator must be consistent.","Violation Examples":["wire [7:0] w_slot_a;\nwire [5:0] w_slot_b;\nwire [7:0] w_or;\n\nassign w_or = w_slot_a | w_slot_b;//Violation1"],"Compliance Examples":["wire [7:0] w_slot_a;\nwire [7:0] w_slot_b;\nwire [7:0] w_or;\n\nassign w_or = w_slot_a | w_slot_b;//Compliance 1"]}
{"id":"R-8-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"Simultaneous use of unsigned numbers and signed numbers in an arithmetic expression is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module add ( din1, din2, dout );\ninput signed [1:0] din1;\ninput [1:0] din2;\noutput [2:0] dout;\n\nreg [2:0] dout;\n\nalways @( din1 or din2 )\nbegin\ndout = { din1[1],din1} + {1'b0,din2};//Violation1\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module add ( din1, din2, dout );\ninput [1:0] din1;\ninput [1:0] din2;\noutput [2:0] dout;\n\nreg [2:0] dout;\n\nalways @( din1 or din2 )\nbegin\ndout = {1'b0, din1} + {1'b0, din2};//Compliance 1\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-8-4","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"Using values containing 'x' or 'z' in a relational expression is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["if ( tmp >= 2'b1z )//Violation1\n..."],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-8-5","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"Using values containing 'x' or 'z' in an arithmetic operation is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["reg [1:0] data1;\nreg [1:0] data2;\n\nalways @ (posedge clk_40m)\nif (!rst_n)\ndata2 <= data1+1'bx;//Violation1\nelse\ndata2 <= data1;\n..."],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-8-6","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"In the numerical representation format <bit-width><radix><digits>, the bit width must be consistent with the actual bit width of the value.","Violation Examples":["reg [3:0] tmp;\n\nalways @ (posedge clk_40m)\nif (!rst_n)\ntmp <= 2'd10;//Violation1"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [3:0] tmp;\n\nalways @ (posedge clk_40m)\nif (!rst_n)\ntmp <= 4'd10;//Compliance 1"]}
{"id":"R-8-7","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"Bit-width overflow of arithmetic operation results is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["wire[7:0] tmp;//Violation1\nreg[7:0] tmp1;\nreg[7:0] tmp2;\n\nassign tmp = tmp1 + tmp2;"],"Compliance Examples":["wire[8:0] tmp;//Compliance 1\nreg[7:0] tmp1;\nreg[7:0] tmp2;\n\nassign tmp = {1'b0, tmp1} + {1'b0, tmp2};"]}
{"id":"A-8-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"Using logical operators in vector operations is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["reg [1:0]data1;\nreg [1:0] data2;\nwire [1:0] out_reg;\n\nassign out_reg = data1&&data2;//Violation1"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-8-2","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Operators","category_key":"operators","description":"It is recommended to specify the radix ('d, 'b, 'h, 'o) and bit width for parameter data and constants.","Violation Examples":["reg [2:0] in1;\nreg out1;\n…\nalways @( in1 )\nif ( in1 == 'b101)//Violation1\nout1 = 'b0;//Violation2\nelse\nout1 = 'b1;//Violation3"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [2:0] in1;\nreg out1;\n…\nalways @( in1 )\nif ( in1 == 3'b101 )//Compliance 1\nout1 = 1'b0;//Compliance2\nelse\nout1 = 1'b1;//Compliance3"]}
{"id":"R-9-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Assignment Statements and Block Statements","category_key":"assignments_blocks","description":"The data bit width of module ports must be consistent with the data bit width of instantiated signals.","Violation Examples":["module ss3(arg1, arg2, arg3, r_out );\ninput [7:0] arg1;\ninput [7:0]arg2;\ninput [7:0]arg3;\noutput [7:0] r_out;\n...\nendmodule\n\nmodule top( ..., r_out, ... );\n…\noutput [7:0] r_out;\n\nwire [4:0] arg1;//Violation1\nwire [7:0] arg2;\nwire [7:0] arg3;\n...\nss3 inst1 ( .arg1(arg1), .arg2(arg2), .arg3(arg3), .r_out(r_out) );\n...\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module ss3(arg1, arg2, arg3, r_out );\ninput [7:0] arg1;\ninput [7:0]arg2;\ninput [7:0]arg3;\noutput [7:0] r_out;\n...\nendmodule\n\nmodule top( ..., r_out, ... );\n…\noutput [7:0] r_out;\n\nwire [7:0] arg1;//Compliance 1\nwire [7:0] arg2;\nwire [7:0] arg3;\n...\nss3 inst1 ( .arg1(arg1), .arg2(arg2), .arg3(arg3), .r_out(r_out) );\n...\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-9-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Assignment Statements and Block Statements","category_key":"assignments_blocks","description":"The bit width of the left-hand side (LHS) and right-hand side (RHS) of an assignment expression must be consistent.","Violation Examples":["module top ( en, din, dout );\ninput en;\ninput [3:0] din;\noutput [2:0] dout;\n\nreg [2:0] dout;\n\nalways @( en or din )\nbegin\nif ( en )\ndout = din;//Violation1\nelse\ndout = 3'b011;\nend\n\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top ( en, din, dout );\ninput en;\ninput [2:0] din;\noutput [2:0] dout;\n\nreg [2:0] dout;\n\nalways @( en or din )\nbegin\nif ( en )\ndout = din;//Compliance 1\nelse\ndout = 3'b011;\nend\n\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-9-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Assignment Statements and Block Statements","category_key":"assignments_blocks","description":"Combinational circuits must use blocking assignments (=); non-blocking assignments (<=) are prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top(in1,in2,in3,out1);\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\ninput in3;\noutput reg out1;\n\nalways @ ( in1,in2,in3 )\nbegin\ncase ( in1 )\n1'b1 : out1 = in2;\n1'b0 : out1 = in3;\ndefault : out1 <= 1'b0;//Violation1\nendcase\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top(in1,in2,in3,out1);\ninput in1;\ninput in2;\ninput in3;\noutput reg out1;\n\nalways @( in1,in2,in3 )\nbegin\ncase ( in1 )\n1'b1 : out1 = in2;\n1'b0 : out1 = in3;\ndefault : out1 = 1'b0;//Compliance 1\nendcase\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-9-4","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Assignment Statements and Block Statements","category_key":"assignments_blocks","description":"Sequential circuits must use non-blocking assignments (<=); blocking assignments (=) are prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top(clk_40m, rst_p, data, dout);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_p;\ninput data;\noutput reg dout;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or posedge rst_p )\nbegin\nif ( rst_p )\ndout = 1'b0;//Violation1\nelse\ndout <= data;\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top(clk_40m, rst_p, data, dout);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_p;\ninput data;\noutput reg dout;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or posedge rst_p )\nbegin\nif (rst_p )\ndout <= 1'b0;//Compliance 1\nelse\ndout <= data;\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-9-5","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Assignment Statements and Block Statements","category_key":"assignments_blocks","description":"Repeatedly assigning values to the same signal under the same condition is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top(clk_40m, rst_n, in0, outx);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in0;\noutput reg[3:0] outx;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )\nbegin\nif ( !rst_n )\noutx <= 4'h0;\nelse begin\noutx <= outx << 1'b1;\noutx[0] <= in0;//Violation1\nend\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top(clk_40m,rst_n,in0,outx);\ninput clk_40m;\ninput rst_n;\ninput in0;\noutput reg[3:0] outx;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m or negedge rst_n )\nbegin\nif ( !rst_n )\noutx <= 4'h0;\nelse begin\noutx[3:1] <= outx[2:0];\noutx[0] <= in0;//Compliance 1\nend\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-9-6","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Assignment Statements and Block Statements","category_key":"assignments_blocks","description":"Delay statements (#) are prohibited.","Violation Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m ) begin\n#1 out <= in;//Violation1\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m ) begin\nout <= in;//Compliance 1\nend"]}
{"id":"R-10-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"A default branch must be used in a case statement.","Violation Examples":["module mux4 ( sel, out1 );\ninput [3:0] sel;\noutput reg [1:0] out1;\n\nalways @ ( sel )\nbegin\ncase ( sel )\n4'b0001 : out1 = 2'b00;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b01;\n4'b0100 : out1 = 2'b10;\n4'b1000 : out1 = 2'b11;//Violation1\nendcase\nend\n\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module mux4 ( sel, out1 );\ninput [3:0] sel;\noutput reg [1:0] out1;\n\nalways @ ( sel )\nbegin\ncase ( sel )\n4'b0001 : out1 = 2'b00;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b01;\n4'b0100 : out1 = 2'b10;\n4'b1000 : out1 = 2'b11;\ndefault : out1 = 2'b00;//Compliance 1\nendcase\nend\n\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-10-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Using fixed values in the control expression of a case statement is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["reg [3:0] state;\ncase (1'b1)//Violation1\nstate[0] : ...;\nstate[1] : …;\nstate[2] : …;\nstate[3] : …;\ndefault: …;\nendcase"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [3:0]state;\n\ncase (state )//Compliance 1\n4'b0000: ...;\n4'b0010 : …;\n4'b0100 : …;\n4'b1000 : …;\ndefault: …;\nendcase"]}
{"id":"R-10-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"All branch expressions of a case statement must be within the range of the control expression, and their data bit widths must be consistent.","Violation Examples":["reg [1:0] sel_expr;\nreg tmp ;\n\ncase( sel_expr )\n4'b0101: tmp = 1'b1;//Violation1\n2'b11: tmp = 1'b0;\ndefault : tmp = 1'b0;\nendcase"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [1:0] sel_expr;\nreg tmp ;\n\ncase( sel_expr )\n2'b01 : tmp = 1'b1;//Compliance 1\n2'b11: tmp = 1'b0;\ndefault : tmp =1'b0;\nendcase"]}
{"id":"R-10-4","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Using 'x' or 'z' in the condition expression of an if statement or the control expression of a case statement is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["reg [1:0] tmp1;\n\nalways@( posedge clk_40m)\nbegin\ncase (tmp1 == 2'b1x)//Violation1\n...\nendcase\nend"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-10-5","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Using '|' or '||' to connect sensitive signals is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m || rst_p ) begin//Violation1\nif ( rst_p )\ndata_q <= 1'b0;\nelse\ndata_q <= data_d;\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m or posedge rst_p) begin//Compliance 1\nif (rst_p)\ndata_ q <= 1'b0;\nelse\ndata_ q <= data_d;\nend"]}
{"id":"R-10-6","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Branch statements of a case statement must use constants; variables or logical operations are prohibited.","Violation Examples":["reg [1:0] dsf;\nreg [1:0] sel;\nreg [1:0] data_out;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m ) begin\ncase ( sel )\n2'b00 : data_out <= 2'b00;\n2'b01 : data_out <= 2'b01;\n2'b10 : data_out <= 2'b10;\ndsf : data_out <= 2'b11;//Violation1\ndefault : data_out<=2'b00;\nendcase\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [1:0] sel;\nreg [1:0] data_out;\n\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m ) begin\ncase ( sel )\n2'b00 : data_out <=2'b00;\n2'b01 : data_out <=2'b01;\n2'b10 : data_out <=2'b10;\n2'b11 : data_out<=2'b11;//Compliance 1\ndefault : data_out<=2'b00;\nendcase\nend"]}
{"id":"A-10-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Overlapping branch statements in a case statement are discouraged.","Violation Examples":["reg [3:0] sel;\nreg [1:0] out1;\n\ncase ( sel )\n4'b0001 : out1 = 2'b00;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b01;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b10;//Violation1\n4'b1000 : out1 = 2'b11;\ndefault : out1 = 2'b00;\nendcase"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [3:0] sel;\nreg [1:0] out1;\n\ncase ( sel )\n4'b0001 : out1 = 2'b00;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b01;\n4'b0100 : out1 = 2'b10;//Compliance 1\n4'b1000 : out1 = 2'b11;\ndefault : out1 = 2'b00;\nendcase"]}
{"id":"A-10-2","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Using casex and casez statements is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["casex (sel)//Violation1\n4'bx0x1: out1 = 1'b0;\n4'b0010: out1 = 1'b1;\n4'b0100: out1 = 1'b0;\n4'b1000: out1 = 1'b1;\ndefault: out1 = 1'b1;\nendcase"],"Compliance Examples":["case (sel)//Compliance 1\n4'b0001: out1 = 1'b0;\n4'b0010: out1 = 1'b1;\n4'b0100: out1 = 1'b0;\n4'b1000: out1 = 1'b1;\ndefault: out1 = 1'b1;\nendcase"]}
{"id":"A-10-3","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"Using values containing 'x' in the default branch is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["module mux4 ( sel, out1 );\ninput [3:0] sel;\noutput reg [1:0] out1;\n\nalways @ ( sel )begin\ncase ( sel )\n4'b0001 : out1 = 2'b00;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b01;\n4'b0100 : out1 = 2'b10;\n4'b1000 : out1 = 2'b11;\ndefault : out1 = 2'bxx;//Violation1\nendcase\nend\n\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module mux4 ( sel, out1 );\ninput [3:0] sel;\noutput reg [1:0] out1;\n\nalways @ ( sel )begin\ncase ( sel )\n4'b0001 : out1 = 2'b00;\n4'b0010 : out1 = 2'b01;\n4'b0100 : out1 = 2'b10;\n4'b1000 : out1 = 2'b11;\ndefault : out1 = 2'b00;//Compliance 1\nendcase\nend\n\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"A-10-4","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"The condition expression of an if statement or conditional operator is discouraged from being a vector; it is recommended to consist of 1-bit-wide signals.","Violation Examples":["wire [7:0] sel;//Violation1\nreg [1:0] data_out;\n\nalways @( posedge clk_40m ) begin\nif ( sel)//Violation2\ndata_out <=2'b01;\nelse\ndata_out <=2'b00;\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["wire sel;//Compliance 1\nreg [1:0] data_out;\n\nalways @( posedge clk_40m) begin\nif ( sel )//Compliance2\ndata_out <=2'b01;\nelse\ndata_out <=2'b00;\nend"]}
{"id":"A-10-5","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Branching Statements","category_key":"branching","description":"It is recommended that if statements in combinational logic circuits end with an else statement.","Violation Examples":["module data_ctrl ( data1, gate, q_data );\ninput data1;\ninput gate;\noutput reg q_data;\n\nalways @ ( data1 or gate ) begin\nif ( gate )//Violation1\nq_data = data1;\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module data_ctrl ( data1, data2, gate, q_data );\ninput data1;\ninput data2;\ninput gate;\noutput reg q_data;\n\nalways @( data1 or gate or data2 ) begin\nif ( gate )\nq_data = data1;\nelse//Compliance 1\nq_data = data2;\nend\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-11-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Loop Statements","category_key":"loop","description":"The initial value and condition of a for statement must be constants, and modifying the loop variable is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["parameter N = 8'd100;\ninteger i,j;\nreg [7:0] reg_a;\nreg [15:0] accum_1;\nreg [15:0] accum_2;\nreg [15:0] accum_3;\n…\nfor( i = reg_a; i < N; i = i+1 ) begin//Violation1\naccum_1= accum_1 + i;\nend\n…\nfor( i = 0; i < reg_a; i = i+1 ) begin//Violation2\naccum_2 = accum_2 + i;\nend\n…\nfor( i = 0; i < N; j = i + 1 ) begin//Violation3\naccum_3 = accum_3 + i;\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["parameter N = 8'd100;\ninteger i;\nreg [15:0] accum;\n…\nfor ( i = 0; i <= N; i = i + 1 )begin//Compliance 1\naccum = accum + i;\nend"]}
{"id":"R-11-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Loop Statements","category_key":"loop","description":"Performing arithmetic operations on variables other than the loop variable in a for statement is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["parameter LOOP = 4'd8;\nreg [4:0] reg_s [7:0];\n…\nfor( i = 0; i < LOOP; i = i + 1 ) begin\nif( i > someb-1)//Violation1\nreg_s[i] = i + 1;\nelse\nreg_s[i] = 0 ;\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["parameter LOOP = 4'd8;\nreg [4:0] reg_s [7:0];\n…\nsomec = someb-1;\nfor( i = 0; i < LOOP; i = i + 1 ) begin\nif( i > somec )//Compliance 1\nreg_s[i] = i + 1;\nelse\nreg_s[i] = 0;\nend"]}
{"id":"R-11-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Loop Statements","category_key":"loop","description":"The reset section and logic section are prohibited from appearing in the same for loop.","Violation Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m or posedge rst_p )\nfor ( i = 0; i <= 3; i = i + 1 )begin\nif ( rst_p )\nout[i] <= 1'b0;//Violation1\nelse\nout[i] <= data[i];//Violation2\nend"],"Compliance Examples":["always @( posedge clk_40m or posedge rst_p )begin\nif ( rst_p )\nfor ( i = 0; i <= 3; i = i + 1 )//Compliance 1\nout[i] <= 1'b0;\nelse\nfor ( i = 0; i <= 3; i = i + 1 )//Compliance2\nout[i] <= data[i];\nend"]}
{"id":"R-11-4","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Loop Statements","category_key":"loop","description":"A loop statement must satisfy the loop condition at least once.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-11-5","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Loop Statements","category_key":"loop","description":"Calling recursive functions is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["function integer factorial( input integer num );\nif ( num <= 1'b1 )\nfactorial = 1'b1;\nelse\nfactorial = num * factorial( num - 1'b1 );//Violation1\n…"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-11-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Loop Statements","category_key":"loop","description":"Using variables in the expression of a repeat statement is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["module top ( ..., data_in, ... );\n...\ninput [7:0] data_in;\n...\nrepeat (data_in) data_out = data_out + 1'd1;//Violation1\n...\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top ( ... );\n...\nrepeat (20) data_out = data_out + 1'd1;//Compliance 1\n...\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-12-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"Using timing control statements in a task statement is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module d32_ang( ... );\ntask swap;\n...\nalways @ ( posedge clk_40m)begin//Violation1\n…\nend\n\nendtask\n...\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-12-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"Using initial statements is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module d32_ang( ... );\nreg out;\n\ninitial//Violation1\nbegin\nout = 1'b0;\nend\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module d32_ang( ... );\nreg out;\n\nalways @(posedge clk_40m or posedge rst_p)//Compliance 1\nif (rst_p)\nbegin\nout <= 1'b0;\nend\nelse\nout <= 1'b1;\n…\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-12-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"Using non-blocking assignments (<=) in a function statement is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["function add_sub;\ninput arg_1;\ninput arg_2;\ninput op_sel;\n\nreg res;\n\nbegin\nif (op_sel == 1'b1 )\nres <= arg_1;//Violation1\nelse\nres <= arg_2;//Violation2\n\nadd_sub = res;\nend\nendfunction"],"Compliance Examples":["function add_sub;\ninput arg_1;\ninput arg_2;\ninput op_sel;\n\nreg res;\n\nbegin\nif (op_sel == 1'b1 )\nres = arg_1;//Compliance 1\nelse\nres = arg_2;//Compliance2\n\nadd_sub = res;\nend\nendfunction"]}
{"id":"R-12-4","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"In function and task statements, assigning values to global signals is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top;\n...\nreg glb;\n\nfunction func1;\ninput data_a;\ninput data_b;\n\nbegin\nif (data_a )\nfunc1 = data_b;\nelse begin\nglb = data_a;//Violation1\nfunc1=data_b+1'b1;\nend\nend\nendfunction\n…\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-12-5","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"In a function statement, the bit width of the return value must be consistent with the bit width of the input signals.","Violation Examples":["function sum;\ninput [3:0] a,b;\nbegin\nsum = a + b;//Violation1\nend\nendfunction"],"Compliance Examples":["function [4:0] sum;\ninput [3:0] a,b;\nbegin\nsum = a + b;//Compliance1\nend\nendfunction"]}
{"id":"R-12-6","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"In a task statement, the bit width of the input signals must be consistent with the bit width of the output signals.","Violation Examples":["reg data2;\nwire [1:0] data1;//Violation1\n\nalways @(posedge clk_40m)\nbegin\nlight(data1, data2);//Violation2\n...\nend\n\ntask light;\ninput data1;//Violation3\noutput data2;\n\nbegin\ndata2 = !data1;\nend\nendtask"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-12-7","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"Using feedback in combinational logic circuits is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["module top ( data, sel, qout );\ninput [1:0] data;\ninput sel;\noutput qout;\n\nwire [2:0] temp;\n\nassign temp[0] = data[0] & temp[2];//Violation1\nassign temp[1] = temp[0] ^ data[1];\nassign temp[2] = sel? data[0] : temp[1];\nassign qout = temp[2];\n...\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top ( data, sel, qout );\ninput [1:0] data;\ninput sel;\noutput qout;\n\nwire [2:0] temp;\n\nassign temp[0] = data[0] ;//Compliance 1\nassign temp[1] = temp[0] ^ data[1];\nassign temp[2] = sel? data[0] : temp[1];\nassign qout = temp[2];\n...\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"R-12-8","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"Array index out-of-bounds is prohibited.","Violation Examples":["reg [31:0] in1 [10:0];\nreg [31:0] data;\n\nassign data = in1 [ 8'h10 ];//Violation1"],"Compliance Examples":["reg [31:0] in1 [10:0];\nreg [31:0] data;\n\nassign data = in1 [ 8'd10 ];//Compliance 1"]}
{"id":"R-12-9","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"Sensitive signals in the sensitivity list must be complete, with no omissions or redundancies.","Violation Examples":["module top(in1,in2,in3,out1);\ninput in1;\ninputin2;\ninputin3;\noutput reg out1;\n\nalways @ ( in1, in2 )//Violation1\nbegin\nout1 = in1 & in2 & in3;\nend\n\nendmodule"],"Compliance Examples":["module top(in1,in2,in3,out1);\ninput in1;\ninputin2;\ninputin3;\noutput reg out1;\n\nalways @ ( in1, in2, in3 )//Compliance 1\nbegin\nout1 = in1 & in2 & in3;\nend\n\nendmodule"]}
{"id":"A-12-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Structural Constructs","category_key":"structural_constructs","description":"It is recommended that array indices be simple signals; using expressions is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["reg [2:0] sel;\nreg [31:0] res [20:0];\nreg [31:0] out1;\n\nassign out1 = res [(sel*2+1)];//Violation1"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-14-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"FSM Structure","category_key":"fsm","description":"Deadlock states and unreachable states in a state machine are prohibited.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-14-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"FSM Structure","category_key":"fsm","description":"In the default state of a state machine, all registers in the state machine must be reset to a deterministic state (reset state or idle state).","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-14-3","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"FSM Structure","category_key":"fsm","description":"A state machine must have an initial state.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-14-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"FSM Structure","category_key":"fsm","description":"It is recommended that the number of states in a single state machine does not exceed 40.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-14-2","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"FSM Structure","category_key":"fsm","description":"It is recommended to minimize the number of bit changes during state transitions of a state machine.","Violation Examples":["//State Machine Defination//Violation1\nparameter STATE_IDLE = 3'b000;\nparameter STATE_STEP1 = 3'b001;\nparameter STATE_STEP2 = 3'b010;\nparameter STATE_STEP3 = 3'b011;\nparameter STATE_STEP4 = 3'b100;\nparameter STATE_STEP5 = 3'b101;\nparameter STATE_STEP6 = 3'b110;\nparameter STATE_STOP = 3'b111;"],"Compliance Examples":["// State Machine Defination（Gray Code）//Compliance 1\nparameter STATE_IDLE = 3'b000;\nparameter STATE_STEP1 = 3'b001;\nparameter STATE_STEP2 = 3'b011;\nparameter STATE_STEP3 = 3'b010;\nparameter STATE_STEP4 = 3'b110;\nparameter STATE_STEP5 = 3'b111;\nparameter STATE_STEP6 = 3'b101;\nparameter STATE_STOP = 3'b100;\n\n// State Machine Defination（One-Hot Code）// Compliance 2\nparameter STATE_IDLE = 7'b0000000;\nparameter STATE_STEP1 = 7'b0000001;\nparameter STATE_STEP2 = 7'b0000010;\nparameter STATE_STEP3 = 7'b0000100;\nparameter STATE_STEP4 = 7'b0001000;\nparameter STATE_STEP5 = 7'b0010000;\nparameter STATE_STEP6 = 7'b0100000;\nparameter STATE_STOP = 7'b1000000;"]}
{"id":"R-16-1","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Synthesis-Related Coding Guidelines","category_key":"synthesis","description":"Modifying the reset attributes of code using synthesis tools is prohibited. Note: It is better to modify reset attributes in the code.","Violation Examples":["//synthesis async_set_reset\"set\"//Violation1\nalways @( posedge clk_40m )\nif ( set )\nq1 <= 1'b1;\nelse\nq1 <= data;"],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"R-16-2","type":"required","severity_default":"Critical","category":"Synthesis-Related Coding Guidelines","category_key":"synthesis","description":"The state machine compilation mode must be set to \"safe\" mode.","Violation Examples":[],"Compliance Examples":[]}
{"id":"A-16-1","type":"advisory","severity_default":"Medium","category":"Synthesis-Related Coding Guidelines","category_key":"synthesis","description":"Using the \"full_case\" attribute is discouraged.","Violation Examples":["case(data) //synopsys full_case//Violation1\n8'b00000001 : code =32'd0;\n8'b00000010 : code =32'd1;\n8'b00000100 : code =32'd2;\n8'b00001000 : code =32'd3;\n8'b00010000 : code =32'd4;\n8'b00100000 : code =32'd5;\n8'b01000000 : code =32'd6;\n8'b10000000 : code =32'd7;\ndefault : code =32'd0;\nendcase"],"Compliance Examples":["case(data)//Compliance 1\n8'b00000001 : code =32'd0;\n8'b00000010 : code =32'd1;\n8'b00000100 : code =32'd2;\n8'b00001000 : code =32'd3;\n8'b00010000 : code =32'd4;\n8'b00100000 : code =32'd5;\n8'b01000000 : code =32'd6;\n8'b10000000 : code =32'd7;\ndefault : code =32'd0;\nendcase\n\n52\n\n1"]}
